  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_0' aria-label=\" Ranjit Sarkar versus Ravi Ganesh Bhardwaj and Others pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('0','2025','2025_3_1448_1459','2025INSC415'); ><font size='4'> <strong>RANJIT SARKAR<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>RAVI GANESH BHARDWAJ AND OTHERS </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 3 S.C.R. 1448</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 415</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010004732025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : DIPANKAR DATTA<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, MANMOHAN</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Whether in the instant case, the Judicial Magistrate in terms of s.256, Cr.PC was justified in dismissing the complaint for default vide order dated 16.04.2021. Headnotes&dagger; Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 &ndash; s.256 &ndash; Appellant lodged a complaint alleging issued process &ndash; Respondent arrayed as accused therein filed an application u/s. 482 Cr.PC (CRR No. 2327 of 2018) and sought quashing of summons &ndash; The High Court stayed proceedings &ndash; Owing to outbreak of COVID, there was national lockdown &ndash; Despite the aforesaid stay,<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 17-03-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CRIMINAL APPEAL No. 1593/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('0','2025','2025_3_1448_1459','2025INSC415','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='co